

Security Model
  * Foundation is each message has associated client UUID 
  * Client either does or does not have read/write access to a pool
  * Network layer is responsible for ensuring this is reliable
  * Leverage graph model to reduce/eliminate searching
  * Pools are aggregated into PoolAuthGroups (so pools with same creds can be aggregated)
  * PoolAuthGroups point to individual clients and/or CertAuthAuthorities
  * Storage nodes pre-load cred info on startup for all PoolAuthGroups referenced by its hosted pools

aspen.base.FinalizationActionsRegistrar
  * object that uses a list of FinalizationActionFactory
  * kvtree.FinalizationActions implements the Factory and provides UUIDs for the FAs it supports
  * Need to implement stubbed section
  * Need to consider having Client run the FA list (maybe heartbeat to designated node so it delays action)

